### LESSON 252: SMOKE TEST — CREATE A NEW TODO
# This file is consumed by the REST Client VS Code extension
# (https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=humao.rest-client).
# Clicking "Send Request" above the line starting with POST fires the request
# directly from the editor and opens the response in a side panel. Any other
# HTTP client (curl, Postman, HTTPie, ...) can reproduce the same call.
#
# The Content-Type header is what triggers Express's `express.json()`
# middleware to parse the body below and expose it as `req.body` inside the
# route handler. Remove the header and `req.body.text` would come through as
# undefined.
POST http://localhost:3000/todos
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Some new todo."
}
